\pard\f0\fs28 Tubers usually 2, ovoid or subglobose, entire. Stem with numerous leaves. Flowers in a dense spike. Outer lateral perianth-segments patent, the outer median connivent with the inner lateral to form a galea. Labellum deeply 3-lobed, with 2 longitudinal ridges at the base. Spur long, directed downwards. Column short. Rostellum small. Viscidium solitary, transversely elongate, bearing 2 pollinia; bursicle simple.
